{
  "texts": [
    "This result represents an example of how sMTJs could be used to reduce footprint and energy consumption in the CMOS underlayer.",
    "In this work, we present a small example of a CMOS + sMTJ system, however, similar systems can be scaled up to much bigger densities, leveraging the proven manufacturability of magnetic memory at gigabit densities.",
    "Our results will help lay the groundwork for larger implementations in the presence of unavoidable device-to-device variations.",
    "We also focus beyond the common use case of combinatorial optimization of similar physical computers 33, considering probabilistic inference and learning in deep energy-based models.",
    "Specifically, we use our system to train 3-hidden 1-visible layer deep and unrestricted Boltzmann machines that entirely rely on the asynchronous dynamics of the stochastic MTJs."
  ]
}